    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2008-03-12</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-06-03T20:27:05Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Save Lives First Act of 2008 - Amends the United States Leadership Against HIV/AIDS, Tuberculosis, and Malaria Act of 2003 to allocate FY2009-FY2013 HIV/AIDS assistance as follows: (1) at least 55% for therapeutic medical care of individuals infected with HIV; and (2) at least 5% percent to expand the use of rapid HIV/AIDS testing, of which at least 25% shall be expended for assistance to countries that have adopted a national policy of universal rapid HIV/AIDS diagnosis of all patients of publicly funded facilities, including pregnant women and newborns.</p> <p>Requires the President to ensure that, by the end of FY2013, specified HIV/AIDS treatment, testing, and intervention goals have been met.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
